verbose_text: As a result, in MRC-5 cells, inhibition of the NF-kappaB pathway with BMS-345541 (10 muM) significantly inhibited PIV induced cytokines, namely, IL-1beta, 1ra, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, IFN-gamma, TNF-alpha, G-CSF, GM-CSF, IP-10, eotaxin, RANTES, PDGF-bb, and VEGF.
evidence: NF-kappaB pathway with BMS-345541 (10 muM) significantly inhibited PIV-induced cytokines, namely, IL-1beta, 1ra, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, IFN-gamma
